}}</ref>

==Research on WDU (Weapons Derived Uranium)==

Busby had written repeatedly on [[Depleted uranium|DU]] <ref>''Depleted Science: the health consequences and mechanisms of exposure to fallout from Depleted Uranium weapons'' in ''The Trojan Horses of Nuclear War'' M. Kuepker and D. Kraft eds. Hamburg, 2004</ref><ref>''Depleted Uranium Weapons, metal particles and radiation dose'' European J. Biology and Bioelectromagnetics 2005, 1(1) 82-93</ref><ref>''Does uranium contamination amplify natural background radiation dose to the DNA?'' European J. Biology and Bioelectromagnetics 2005, 1(2) 120-131</ref><ref>''Depleted Uranium. Why all the fuss?'' United Nations Disarmament Forum Journal UNIDIR, Nov 2008</ref> and given presentations at the Royal Society, London,<ref>"Science on Trial: On the Biological Effects and Health Risks following exposure to aerosols produced by the use of DU weapons" Invited presentation to the Royal Society, London July 19, 2000 (also given at the Int. Conference against DU, Manchester, Nov. 4) and on "Health effects of Depleted Uranium (again)" in 2001</ref> where he again gave a talk in Nov. 2008, titled "Scientific Dishonesty" <ref>[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dOI-wpMlq28 Dr Chris Busby at the Royal Society: Scientific Dishonesty]</ref> and he reported or published the following findings:
* "a statistically significant increase in uranium in all the filters beginning at the start of the 2nd Gulf War (03-04/2003) and ending when it ended" from analysis of data—obtained using [[Freedom of information legislation|FOIA]]—from high volume air samplers, deployed by the [[Atomic Weapons Establishment|AWE]] Aldermaston<!-- A-bomb-factory -->, Berkshire(UK) <ref>[http://www.mindfully.org/Nucs/2006/DU-Europe-Contamination1jan06.htm Did the use of uranium weapons in Gulf War 2 result in contamination of Europe?] Chris Busby and Saoirse Morgan; March 1, 2006, ''European J. Biology and Bioelectromagnetics''</ref>
* isotopic signatures showing EU (slightly Enriched Uranium) in a veteran of [[1995 NATO bombing campaign in Bosnia and Herzegovina|the
Bosnia theatre]] in 1996 <ref>[http://www.euradcom.org/publications/ecrruraniumrept.pdf Uranium and Health: The Health Effects of Exposure to Uranium and Uranium Weapons Fallout] Chris Busby; Documents of the ECRR 2010 No 2</ref><ref>Ballardie FW, Cowley R, Cox A, Curry A, Denley H, Denton J, Dick J, Gerquin-Kern J-L, Redmond A, ''A man who brought the war home with him'' The Lancet, Vol. 372 No. 9653 p 1926</ref>
* EU from "guided weapons employed by the Israeli military..in..soil samples from bomb craters in southern Lebanon" <ref>[http://www.llrc.org/du/subtopic/lebanrept.pdf C, Williams D, ''Evidence of Enriched Uranium in guided weapons employed by the Israeli Military in Lebanon in July 2006''] Research Note 6/2006 Aberystwyth: Green Audit</ref> and in the air filter of an ambulance, stating "The measurements made in the air filter show that at least part of [[Beirut]] has been contaminated and that the Uranium use was not restricted to areas near [[Khiam]], where the Uranium was first detected by our sampling."<ref>[http://www.llrc.org/du/subtopic/ambulance.pdf Busby Busby Chris and Williams Dai, ''Further Evidence of Enriched Uranium in guided weapons employed by the Israeli Military in Lebanon in July 2006: Ambulance Air Filter Analysis''] Green Audit Research Note 7/2006 Nov 3rd 2006</ref>
* "Cancer, Infant Mortality and Birth Sex-Ratio in [[Fallujah]], Iraq 2005–2009" <ref>[http://www.mdpi.com/1660-4601/7/7/2828/pdf Cancer, Infant Mortality and Birth Sex-Ratio in Fallujah, Iraq 2005–2009] Chris Busby, Malak Hamdan, Entesar Ariabi; ''International Journal of Environmental Research and Public Health'' 7, 2828-2837, July 6, 2010; doi:10.3390/ijerph7072828</ref> 'worse than Hiroshima' <ref>[http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/toxic-legacy-of-us-assault-on-fallujah-worse-than-hiroshima-2034065.html Toxic legacy of US assault on Fallujah 'worse than Hiroshima'] Robert Cockburn, ''The Independent'' July 24, 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.counterpunch.org/patrick07272010.html Worse Than Hiroshima? - The Toxic Legacy From the Siege of Fallujah] Robert Cockburn, ''counterpunch.org'', July 27, 2010</ref>
* EU "in hair from the parents of children with congenital anomalies in Fallujah" in 2011 <ref>[http://www.conflictandhealth.com/content/5/1/15 Uranium and other contaminants in hair from the parents of children with congenital anomalies in Fallujah, Iraq] Samira Alaani1, Muhammed Tafash, Christopher Busby, Malak Hamdan and Eleonore Blaurock-Busch; ''Conflict and Health'' 2011, 5:15; doi:10.1186/1752-1505-5-15</ref>
In November 2012, Busby gave a talk in Geneva at the [[Human Rights Council]] <!-- 's session 'Roundtable on Human Rights Issues that Require the Council's Attention: Iraq.' --><ref>[http://www.canadafreepress.com/index.php/article/49520 Obama-backed UN “Human Rights” Council Facilitates US-bashing Meet] by Anne Bayefsky</ref> about the failures of radiation protection as a Human Rights Issue.<ref>[http://justiceforiraq.blogspot.co.at/2012/09/press-release.html Birth Defects study in Fallujah Iraq] (Press release)</ref>

